      <p class="list-title is-inline-block"><a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/math/0004005">arXiv:math/0004005</a>
        <span>&nbsp;[<a href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/math/0004005">pdf</a>, <a href="https://arxiv.org/ps/math/0004005">ps</a>, <a href="https://arxiv.org/format/math/0004005">other</a>]&nbsp;</span>
      </p>
      <div class="tags is-inline-block">
        <span class="tag is-small is-link tooltip is-tooltip-top" data-tooltip="Rings and Algebras">math.RA</span>
        </div>
      
    </div>
    
    <p class="title is-5 mathjax">
      
        Matrix Theory over the Complex Quaternion Algebra
      
    </p>
    <p class="authors">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Authors:</span>
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Tian%2C+Y">Yongge Tian</a>
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="math/0004005v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        We present in this paper some fundamental tools for developing matrix analysis over the complex quaternion algebra. As applications, we consider generalized inverses, eigenvalues and eigenvectors, similarity, determinants of complex quaternion matrices, and so on.
        
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="math/0004005v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
          We present in this paper some fundamental tools for developing matrix analysis over the complex quaternion algebra. As applications, we consider generalized inverses, eigenvalues and eigenvectors, similarity, determinants of complex quaternion matrices, and so on.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('math/0004005v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('math/0004005v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
      </span>
    </p>
    

    <p class="is-size-7"><span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Submitted</span> 1 April, 2000; 
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">originally announced</span> April 2000.
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="comments is-size-7">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Comments:</span>
      <span class="has-text-grey-dark mathjax">15 pages, LaTex</span>
    </p>
    

    
      <p class="comments is-size-7">
        
          <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Report number:</span>
          formerly <span class="search-hit mathjax">math.LA</span>/0004005
        

        

        
