    </div>
    
    <p class="title is-5 mathjax">
      
        A simple polynomial time algorithm to approximate the permanent within a simply exponential factor
      
    </p>
    <p class="authors">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Authors:</span>
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Barvinok%2C+A">Alexander Barvinok</a>
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="math/9704218v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        We present a simple randomized polynomial time algorithm to approximate the mixed discriminant of $n$ positive semidefinite $n \times n$ matrices within a factor $2^{O(n)}$. Consequently, the algorithm allows us to approximate in randomized polynomial time the permanent of a given $n \times n$ non-negative matrix within a factor $2^{O(n)}$. When applied to approximating the permanent, the algori&hellip;
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('math/9704218v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('math/9704218v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="math/9704218v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
          We present a simple randomized polynomial time algorithm to approximate the mixed discriminant of $n$ positive semidefinite $n \times n$ matrices within a factor $2^{O(n)}$. Consequently, the algorithm allows us to approximate in randomized polynomial time the permanent of a given $n \times n$ non-negative matrix within a factor $2^{O(n)}$. When applied to approximating the permanent, the algorithm turns out to be a simple modification of the well-known Godsil-Gutman estimator.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('math/9704218v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('math/9704218v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
      </span>
    </p>
    

    <p class="is-size-7"><span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Submitted</span> 8 April, 1997; 
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">originally announced</span> April 1997.
      
    </p>
    

    
      <p class="comments is-size-7">
        
          <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Report number:</span>
          MSRI 1997-031, formerly <span class="search-hit mathjax">math.LA</span>/9704218
        

        

        
      </p>
    

    
  </li>

  <li class="arxiv-result">
