    <p class="title is-5 mathjax">
      
        Almost orthogonal submatrices of an orthogonal matrix
      
    </p>
    <p class="authors">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Authors:</span>
      
      <a href="/search/?searchtype=author&amp;query=Rudelson%2C+M">Mark Rudelson</a>
      
    </p>
    
    <p class="abstract mathjax">
      <span class="has-text-black-bis has-text-weight-semibold">Abstract</span>:
      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="math/9606213v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        Let $A$ be an $n \times M$ matrix whose rows are orthonormal. Let $A_I$ be a submatrix of $A$ whose column indexes belong to the set $I$. Given $ε&gt;0$ we estimate the smallest cardinality of the set $I$, such that the operator $A_I$ is an $ε$-isometry.
        
      </span>
      <span class="abstract-full has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="math/9606213v1-abstract-full" style="display: none;">
          Let $A$ be an $n \times M$ matrix whose rows are orthonormal. Let $A_I$ be a submatrix of $A$ whose column indexes belong to the set $I$. Given $ε&gt;0$ we estimate the smallest cardinality of the set $I$, such that the operator $A_I$ is an $ε$-isometry.
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('math/9606213v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'none'; document.getElementById('math/9606213v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'inline';">&#9651; Less</a>
      </span>
